column5: Heading up to Birch Dale Lodge on Eagle Lake on 9/5/18 for our 30th year and will be having our 18th Annual "Wing Night" on Saturday 9/8/18 at 7pm in the lodge, if you are in the area stop by and have some wings. Would like to meet my fellow Walleye Central members and put a face to a user name. Terry
Do THIGHS.... They are cheaper and taste better...
Narda, we are driving up on the 8th and should be in the area around that time. If so, we will stop by to at least say hello and possibly consume an adult beverage based on rye.
Sure but the delivery fee would be quite substantial!
Very tempted,have to check my social calendar
NARDA, we will be passing by about 9am. Plan on fishing by noon. If you hear a horn about 9am that will be us!
I'd like to be your guest on the 7th.
